1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
Science has a clearer story about VAERS limitations than social media does.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:10,400
VAERS, or the Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System, collects data on vaccine side effects.

3
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:14,800
But here’s the catch: VAERS reports can be incomplete and unverified.

4
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:18,400
Studies show that many reports are coincidental, not causal.

5
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:19,200
Context matters.

6
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:24,800
Understanding these limitations helps us see the bigger picture—vaccines are still safe and effective.

7
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:25,600
Stay informed.

8
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:29,600
Like and share for more insights on health and science.
